/**
 * CamBot - a one-node 3D camera you direct from a shape-layer target that hosts the controls.
 *
 * @name CamBot
 * @author IVG Design
 * @version 3.15.1
 * @date 2026-07-12
 * @license MIT
 * @ui HEADLESS
 *
 * @description
 * Builds a complete 3D camera rig you direct from a single effect panel: a camera plus a
 * "CamBot N Target" control-host shape whose every channel (position, orientation, roll, zoom,
 * focus, aperture, blur) is expression-driven, so you animate controls and never the camera. A
 * Look-At-Influence dial crossfades from a genuine one-node free/FPS camera to a two-node
 * tracking cam with no mode switch, and a Moves engine performs 26 procedural camera moves off a
 * single Progress slider.
 *
 * @functionality
 * • Creates a camera + control-host shape layer; wires all camera channels via expressions
 * • Look-At-Influence dial: one-node free camera (0) <-> two-node tracking (100), smooth crossfade
 * • Orientation-driven aim (auto-orient off): X/Y Rotation locked to 0, Z Rotation = Roll — all
 *   rotation channels rig-owned so mode changes leave no stray values
 * • Multi-target blending: duplicate the CamBot Target controller, point each at a layer, animate
 *   Target Influence to hand off the aim through the weighted midpoint
 * • Lens in millimetres (Focal Length + Film Width -> Zoom), smart auto-focus DOF, F-Stop,
 *   near/far blur, focus-area width; Realistic Limits clamp for physically plausible values
 * • Handheld shake (position + aim), follow smoothing, Dolly, Orbit / Orbit Elevation
 * • Moves engine: 26 procedural moves driven by a Progress slider, resized by Move Shaping
 *   controls (Radius/Depth/Height in px, Turns count, Spin degrees) that auto-fill per move
 *
 * @usage
 * 1. Open a composition and run CamBot — it builds "CamBot N Target" (shape) and "CamBot N Cam"
 * 2. Direct the camera from the CamBot effect on the target shape; move the shape to re-aim
 * 3. For tracking, raise Look-At-Influence and point a CamBot Target controller at a layer
 * 4. For a move, pick one from Move and keyframe Progress 0->100
 *
 * @requirements
 * • Adobe After Effects CC or later
 * • An active composition
 * • "Allow Scripts to Write Files and Access Network" enabled (first run registers the pseudo
 *   effects from temporary .ffx files)
 *
 * @changelog
 * 3.15.1 - Swoop follows a curved quarter-ellipse arc (vertical vs forward move on different
 *          phases) instead of a straight diagonal.
 * 3.15.0 - Swoop High/Low are now arrival moves: start high/low + off to the side and swoop IN to
 *          the framed shot at Progress 100 (were fly-by passes that ended behind).
 * 3.14.1 - Re-embedded CamBot.ffx with the Move Shaping controls (Radius/Depth/Height/Turns/Spin).
 * 3.14.0 - Move Shaping now ABSOLUTE: Radius/Depth/Height (px), Turns (count), Spin (deg). Engine
 *          uses them directly, falling back to D-scaled geometry until the controls exist. The
 *          script sets a default(Move)+value expression on each so it shows the move's size and
 *          stays scrubbable (default sized off comp width - live camera dist would be circular).
 * 3.13.0 - Move Shaping: moves read Radius/Depth/Height/Turns (x multipliers, default 100%) and
 *          Spin (added longitudinal roll). Read via try/catch so it is inert until the controls
 *          are added to the effect. Helix uses all five; Spin applies to any active move.
 * 3.12.1 - Re-embedded CamBot.ffx (Look-At-Influence moved into the Focus group).
 * 3.12.0 - True one-node: auto-orient off; aim drives Orientation (blend of free-dir <-> target-
 *          dir via lookAt). X/Y Rotation locked to 0, Z Rotation = Roll. No POI. All rotation
 *          channels are expression-owned, so mode switches can't leave stray values.
 * 3.11.0 - Auto-Focus fades to Manual by the effective look-at, so one-node (no target) focuses
 *          manually; POI and DOF focus plane now agree everywhere.
 * 3.10.1 - One-node POI now sits at the (stable) Manual Focus Distance straight ahead instead
 *          of the auto-focus distance, so it no longer drifts when the camera moves.
 * 3.10.0 - Target model: aim is purely the weighted CamBot Target controllers (no host
 *          fallback). Effective look-at = Look-At-Influence x total target influence, so
 *          zero targeted -> one-node even at 100%. CamBot Target 1 defaults to self@100.
 * 3.9.1 - First target uses addProperty (exactly one instance) instead of applyPreset, which
 *         was replaying the multiple instances saved in CamBotTarget.ffx.
 * 3.9.0 - Simplified: no Target picker on main; layers now "CamBot N Target" / "CamBot N Cam".
 *         A "CamBot Target 1" controller is applied up front - duplicate it for more targets
 *         (auto-numbers); no cmd/ctrl branch. Aim iterates CamBot Target 1..N.
 * 3.8.0 - Multi-target aim is now a weighted average (equal influences -> midpoint) instead of
 *         a successive lerp; the primary fills the remaining weight under 1.
 * 3.7.2 - add-target no longer creates a null; it just drops another "CamBot Target" effect on
 *         the shape - point its Target Layer at any existing layer and keyframe the influence.
 * 3.7.1 - Fix add-target crash: modifier branch ran before targetEffectData was assigned
 *         (var-hoisting) -> moved below the data decls. add-target creates the null first.
 * 3.7.0 - Added Helix In/Out (corkscrew: helix around the view axis, wide<->narrow) at 14/15;
 *         shifted Fly-By..Drift to 16-27. Re-embedded 27-item CamBot.ffx. add-target now
 *         applies the preset directly (fixes the applyEffect crash).
 * 3.6.0 - Re-embedded current CamBot.ffx (new dropdown + Target Appearance + Target) and
 *         CamBotTarget.ffx; embedded CamBotTarget_shape.ffx (self-contained). Smoothing
 *         implemented as trailing-average follow-lag on the target.
 * 3.5.0 - Move dropdown remap: added Swoop High/Low (16/17); shifted Crane..Handheld to
 *         18-25; removed Breathe + Rack Focus. 25 moves total.
 * 3.4.0 - Target Appearance hooked up: Target Scale -> host scale, Target Opacity -> host
 *         opacity, Target Hide -> opacity 0 (gizmo stays). "Target" picker now overrides the
 *         host as the POI. 3D target ignores lights/shadows.
 * 3.3.0 - cmd/ctrl-run ADDS a target: drops a "CamBot Target" effect (+ aim null) onto the
 *         nearest/selected CamBot Target shape instead of building a new rig.
 * 3.2.0 - Host is now a "CamBot Target" SHAPE layer (effects cannot live on a camera). The
 *         shape carries the rig controls + is the primary target; multi-target via extra
 *         "CamBot Target" effects (Target Layer + Target Influence, auto-numbered) on it.
 * 3.1.0 - POI-driven one-node sim: two-node camera, POI parked straight ahead at the focus
 *         point (blends to target by Influence); aim shake jitters the POI.
 * 3.0.0 - Effect-on-camera topology (reverted - not allowed by AE); move-engine fixes:
 *         dolly-zoom direction, real spiral, fly-through pass-through, reveal, whip-to-target,
 *         no forced tracking, aim shake; toWorld(anchorPoint).
 * 2.0.0 - CamBot rebuild: 25-move procedural engine, Look-At Influence, Dolly/Orbit, mm focal
 *         length, smart focus (auto/rack), handheld shake, Realistic Limits.
 * 1.0.0 - Initial one-node camera rig (Cam Control pseudo-effect).
 *
 * @description
 * Builds a two-node camera plus a "CamBot Target N" shape layer. The shape is the primary
 * target AND hosts the CamBot control effect; the camera reads its controls and aims/positions
 * relative to it. At Look-At-Influence 0 the camera parks its POI straight ahead at the focus
 * point (free feel); as Influence rises it faces the target. Add "CamBot Target" effects to the
 * shape (Target Layer + Target Influence) and animate their influence to blend between subjects.
 *
 * @usage
 * 1. Open or select a comp.  2. Run CamBot -> "CamBot Cam N" + "CamBot Target N" (shape).
 * 3. Direct from the shape's CamBot effect; move the shape to aim; add "CamBot Target" effects
 *    to blend more subjects. Keyframe Progress to play a Move.
 *
 * @notes
 * - The target graphic is applied from CamBotTarget_shape.ffx (referenced by path for now).
 * - Smoothing is temporarily inert (topology change); to be re-implemented.
 */

